{"timestamp": "2026-03-22T20:31:29", "level": "INFO", "logger": "src.query_utils", "message": "Sending text LLM request", "process_id": "telegram-545f94935aff", "user_id": "-", "telegram_user_id": "8634555583", "update_id": "660271818", "action": "telegram_message", "workflow": "-", "os_pid": 69021, "event": "llm_text_request", "response_name": "expense_query_plan", "system_prompt": "You generate safe PostgreSQL read-only queries for a personal expense warehouse. Today's date is 2026-03-22. The only table you may query is fact_expenses(expense_id, user_id, created_at, description, expense_total_amount_in_euros, category). The valid categories are: Lebensmitteleink\u00e4ufe, Kleidung, Dm / Rossmann, Mobilit\u00e4t, Mensa, B\u00e4cker, Taxi / Einzelfahrkarten, Entertainment, Ausgehen (Restaurant / Bar / Kino etc.), Sonstige, Geschenke, Reisen. Requirements: 1. Output exactly one SELECT statement and nothing destructive. 2. Always filter to the current user with `user_id = $1`. 3. Query only fact_expenses. 3a. Do not use CTEs, comments, DDL, DML, or multiple statements. 4. Build efficient queries. For breakdown questions, return a compact grouped result and avoid huge result sets. 5. Prefer the aliases result_value, result_unit, result_label, period_label. 6. Use COALESCE for numeric aggregates when aggregating. 7. Use explicit date ranges when the user names a month. 8. Map groceries or lebensmittel requests to the category 'Lebensmitteleink\u00e4ufe'. 9. explanation must be a short sentence like: I am looking for all expenses in the category \"Lebensmitteleink\u00e4ufe\" for January 2026. 10. response_template must be a short sentence using only {result_value}, {result_unit}, {result_label}, and {period_label}. 11. For grouped breakdowns, keep the result compact, for example with GROUP BY and LIMIT when appropriate. Return only the structured result.", "user_prompt_text": "Today's date: 2026-03-22\nUser message: Wieviel habe ich diesen Monat in den verschiedenen categorien ausgegeben?\nMetadata: {}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-03-22T20:31:31", "level": "INFO", "logger": "src.query_utils", "message": "Received text LLM response", "process_id": "telegram-545f94935aff", "user_id": "-", "telegram_user_id": "8634555583", "update_id": "660271818", "action": "telegram_message", "workflow": "-", "os_pid": 69021, "event": "llm_text_response", "response_name": "expense_query_plan", "model": "gpt-5.4-mini", "response_text": "{\"workflow_type\":\"expense_query\",\"explanation\":\"I am looking for the total expenses for each category in the current month of March 2026.\",\"sql_query\":\"SELECT category AS result_label, COALESCE(SUM(expense_total_amount_in_euros), 0) AS result_value, 'EUR' AS result_unit, 'current month' AS period_label FROM fact_expenses WHERE user_id = $1 AND created_at >= DATE '2026-03-01' AND created_at < DATE '2026-04-01' GROUP BY category ORDER BY result_value DESC, category ASC\",\"response_template\":\"{result_label}: {result_value} {result_unit} in {period_label}\"}"}
